s** (CFI≥0.7)\n2. **Proposed mutation:** A CFI-weighted compression experiment (testing whether filtering by CFI threshold improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n3. **Outcome: REJECTED** — the previous pulse's proposed mutation was moved from `mutations/proposed/` to `mutations/rejected/`\n4. **Proposed mutations waiting: 0** — no new mutation was committed\n\n### State\nThe sandbox is in a loop — it identifies a useful next step (CFI-weighted compression experiment) but rejects its own proposals. No net progress on the research goals. The \"For Next Instantiation\" notes in the session file show the same analysis repeating.\n\n### For Next Instantiation\n- CFI-weighted compression experiment is the clear next concrete action\n- Need to either auto-accept this class of experiment or break the rejection loop somehow"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5030,"output":584,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774365085613}}
